<subSubSection id="C3676519A91BFF86FF651243FBABFBF6" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC23692A91BFF86FF651243FBABFBF6" blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FF651243FEBEFBD3" bold="true" box="[199,314,1071,1096]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Idiosoma elongated, postocularia relative far from each other, dgl- 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FBF61243FBE4FBD3" box="[1108,1120,1071,1096]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
and dgl- 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FB6E1243FB5EFBD3" box="[1228,1242,1071,1096]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
lying anteriorly, gonopore of male with subparallel margins, genital field fused with ventral shield.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676519A91BFF86FF65121BFE27FA16" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC23692A91BFF86FF65121BFC01FAF3" blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FF65121BFED5FB0B" bold="true" box="[199,337,1143,1168]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Description</emphasis>
. Male: Idiosoma elongate, dorsally 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FD5E1214FCA2FB0B" box="[764,806,1144,1168]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="387.0">387</number>
long and 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FC01121BFC49FB0B" box="[931,973,1143,1168]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="255.0">255</number>
wide, ventrally 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FB301214FB38FB0B" box="[1170,1212,1144,1168]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="421.0">421</number>
long. Eyes absent. Dorsal shield with postocularia and four pairs of glandularia, 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FCDF12F0FC23FB2F" box="[893,935,1180,1204]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="372.0">372</number>
long and 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FB8612F0FBCAFB2F" box="[1060,1102,1180,1204]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="198.0">198</number>
wide. Suture lines of coxae incomplete, suture lines of Cx-I and Cx-II distinct, other suture lines indistinct, posterior margin of fourth coxae not visible. A pair of glandularia halfway fourth leg sockets and genital field. Genital field fused with ventral shield, with the three pairs of acetabula lying in a triangle. Gonopore somewhat rectangular, 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FB0C1364FB4EFABB" box="[1198,1226,1288,1312]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="40.0">40</number>
long and 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FA991364FAD3FABB" box="[1339,1367,1288,1312]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="32.0">32</number>
wide. Length/height of P 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FECC1340FEFCFADF" box="[366,376,1324,1348]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
–P 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FE351340FE21FADE" box="[407,421,1324,1349]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
: 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FE131340FE4BFADE" box="[433,463,1324,1349]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="22.0">22</number>
/15, 42/26, 33/23, 
<date id="FFC31052A91BFF86FD3F1340FD5BFADE" box="[669,735,1324,1349]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1962-12-18">62/18</date>
, 28/ 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FCB01340FCAAFADF" box="[786,814,1324,1348]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="12.0">12</number>
. Length of I-leg- 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FC4C1340FB9DFADE" box="[1006,1049,1324,1349]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
: 70, 70, 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FBD91340FB1EFADE" box="[1147,1178,1324,1349]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="68.0">68</number>
. Length of IV-leg- 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FACE1340FA13FADE" box="[1388,1431,1324,1349]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
: 86, 84, 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FF491323FE8EFAF3" box="[235,266,1359,1384]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="52.0">52</number>
. Swimming setae absent. Excretory pore not sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC23692A91BFF86FF651318FE27FA16" blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" box="[199,419,1396,1421]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FF651318FE9AFA16" bold="true" box="[199,286,1396,1421]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Female</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676519A91BFF86FF6513FBFD25FA2B" box="[199,673,1431,1456]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC23692A91BFF86FF6513FBFD25FA2B" blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" box="[199,673,1431,1456]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FF6513FBFEC2FA2B" bold="true" box="[199,326,1431,1456]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named after the 
<typeStatus id="54C68830A91BFF86FDAD13F4FDBBFA2B" box="[527,575,1432,1456]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676519A91BFF86FF6513D0FBA1F986" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC23692A91BFF86FF6513D0FBA1F986" blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FF6513D0FEB0FA4E" bold="true" box="[199,308,1468,1493]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D11A91BFF86FD1213D0FB8EFA4E" authority="K. Viets, 1935" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1935" box="[688,1034,1468,1493]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albaxona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexapora">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FD1213D0FCBAFA4E" box="[688,830,1468,1493]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">A. hexapora</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B63A91BFF86FCF113D0FB86FA4E" author="Viets" box="[851,1026,1468,1493]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda- Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 14, Tropische Binnengewasser, 113 pp." type="book" year="1935">
K. Viets, 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FC6B13D0FB86FA4E" box="[969,1026,1468,1493]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1935.0">1935</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from Java in the more elongated idiosoma. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D11A91BFF86FEB113B3FD31FA63" authority="Lundblad, 1971" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1971" box="[275,693,1503,1528]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albaxona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="javanica">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FEB113B3FE69FA63" box="[275,493,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Albaxona javanica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B63A91BFF86FE5E13B3FD31FA63" author="Lundblad" box="[508,693,1503,1528]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refString="Lundblad, O. (1971) Weitere Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Fliesswassermilben Javas. Arkiv for Zoologie, 23, 293 - 359. [Serie 2]" type="journal article" year="1971">
Lundblad, 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FDDF138CFD31FA63" box="[637,693,1504,1528]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Java shares an elongated idiosoma, but is smaller, the postocularia are closer to each other and dgl- 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FD321068FD18F986" box="[656,668,1540,1565]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
and - 
<number id="3DB524B5A91BFF86FD781068FD6DF987" box="[730,745,1540,1564]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
are located more anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676519A91BFF86FF65104BFCD1F9DB" box="[199,853,1575,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC23692A91BFF86FF65104BFCD1F9DB" blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" box="[199,853,1575,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B909EA80A91BFF86FF65104BFEE4F9DB" bold="true" box="[199,352,1575,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Distribution.</emphasis>
Borneo; known only from the locus typicus.
</paragraph>
